    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "4546" ;
    dc:creator "Huber, Bernhard A.; Carvalho, Leonardo S." ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Filling the gaps: descriptions of unnamed species included in the latest molecular phylogeny of Pholcidae (Araneae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2619118>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2619166> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2619118>
    dc:description "FIGURES 252–263. Epigyna (ventral views), and cleared female genitalia (ventral and dorsal views) of four undescribed Brazilian species of Psilochorus,. 252–254. “Br10-36” from Vargem Alta, Espírito Santo. 255–257. “Br11-147” from Parque Nacional do Pau Brasil, Bahia. 258–260. “Br11-81” from Reserva Biológica de Una, Bahia. 261–263. “Br15-173” from Santa Terezinha, Bahia. pp, pore plates. At various scales." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2619118/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2619166>
    dc:description "FIGURE 348. Known distribution of Psilochorus in the Atlantic Forest of Brazil. Red marks: undescribed species (L.S. Carvalho, B.A. Huber, unpubl. data). Five further South American nominal species are currently assigned to Psilochorus, but their identities and affinities are dubious (see text)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2619166/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

